Reasoning: The paper describes a deep neural network approach for image classification, specifically for melanoma detection. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of transfer learning and fine-tuning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using a pre-trained network as a feature extractor, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the task involves analyzing skin lesion images, which could be considered multimedia (cs.MM).
